data.title: Wings
data.meta_description: Jack Powell and David Armstrong, both in love with Sylvia Lewis, enlist together in the World War I Army Air Corps and become friends. They are sent to France as pilots. Dogfights ensue. In Paris Jack encounters hometown girl Mary Preston, who loves him hopelessly. Later, David, shot down, is believed dead. Jack vows revenge, but mistakenly shoots down David piloting a stolen German plane. A reluctant hero, Jack returns home to faithful Mary Preston.
